1
00:00:03,003 --> 00:00:08,675
WELCOME TO HIKARI CITY!!
1.2 MILES TO TOWN

2
00:00:16,517 --> 00:00:18,060
So it's been three years.

3
00:00:18,894 --> 00:00:21,605
Takao, are you sure you want to do this?

4
00:00:22,814 --> 00:00:23,815
Yeah.

5
00:00:25,651 --> 00:00:28,069
You don't need to, you know.

6
00:00:28,070 --> 00:00:30,530
- We can still--
- I'm all right.

7
00:00:32,241 --> 00:00:35,911
At some point...
I'd have to face it, anyway.

8
00:01:55,407 --> 00:01:57,742
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL

9
00:01:57,743 --> 00:01:59,870
EPISODE 11

10
00:02:01,455 --> 00:02:03,415
Grandpa!

11
00:02:11,882 --> 00:02:13,258
Your sister...

12
00:02:26,188 --> 00:02:29,023
Big Sis...

13
00:02:29,024 --> 00:02:31,860
Haruko...

14
00:02:42,913 --> 00:02:45,164
I really appreciate you coming.

15
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:46,917
We'll see you again tomorrow.

16
00:02:47,417 --> 00:02:49,710
Thank you for taking care of things.

17
00:02:49,711 --> 00:02:51,962
Do you have a place to stay?

18
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:53,715
Yeah. Don't worry about us.

19
00:02:57,594 --> 00:02:58,845
Taka-chan.

20
00:03:04,351 --> 00:03:05,602
You know...

21
00:03:07,854 --> 00:03:10,023
There's one thing I have to say to you.

22
00:03:13,944 --> 00:03:15,529
It's your fault, Taka-chan.

23
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:19,741
No one said it to your face,

24
00:03:20,992 --> 00:03:24,204
but we were all amazed
you had the nerve to show your face.

25
00:03:27,582 --> 00:03:30,335
Do you have any idea
how difficult you made our lives?

26
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:37,342
I bet you didn't get to see
Grandpa at the end

27
00:03:38,427 --> 00:03:41,221
because he rejected you, Taka-chan.

28
00:03:45,642 --> 00:03:47,185
I'm sorry.

29
00:03:52,149 --> 00:03:53,567
I sincerely apologize!

30
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:56,403
If you're actually sorry,

31
00:04:00,157 --> 00:04:02,659
spend the rest of your life
making things right.

32
00:04:14,796 --> 00:04:16,798
You're born in this town

33
00:04:17,883 --> 00:04:19,717
and you die in this town.

34
00:04:19,718 --> 00:04:21,719
We're sorry for your loss.
:cue

35
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:23,971
That was supposed
to be my life, too.

36
00:04:23,972 --> 00:04:25,181
KASUGA FUNERAL

37
00:04:25,182 --> 00:04:26,933
But I got out of this town

38
00:04:27,893 --> 00:04:29,852
and continued to live on.

39
00:04:29,853 --> 00:04:31,353
GUEST SIGN IN

40
00:04:31,354 --> 00:04:33,064
Then, what is this town?

41
00:04:34,024 --> 00:04:35,524
What does it mean to me?

42
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:37,318
MIZUKOSHI INC.
NEIGHBORS

43
00:04:37,319 --> 00:04:39,111
After what he did three years ago...

44
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:40,697
- I'm shocked they showed up.
- Yeah.

45
00:04:42,741 --> 00:04:46,619
-  It is him.
- My goodness. They've got some nerve, no?

46
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:49,122
After causing that much trouble...

47
00:04:59,591 --> 00:05:01,426
Takao, are you doing all right?

48
00:05:02,761 --> 00:05:03,762
Yeah.

49
00:05:06,389 --> 00:05:07,516
Dad,

50
00:05:08,725 --> 00:05:09,935
Mom,

51
00:05:12,771 --> 00:05:14,189
I'm sorry.

52
00:05:18,318 --> 00:05:19,528
Thank you.

53
00:05:23,490 --> 00:05:24,783
Takao...

54
00:05:30,038 --> 00:05:32,791
We're very sorry for your loss.

55
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:39,631
It's been a while.

56
00:05:41,049 --> 00:05:42,592
Kinoshita...

57
00:05:53,854 --> 00:05:54,980
I'm sorry...

58
00:05:55,939 --> 00:05:57,190
about back then.

59
00:05:59,401 --> 00:06:00,777
Right after,

60
00:06:01,361 --> 00:06:04,072
Nanako moved away without even telling me.

61
00:06:06,366 --> 00:06:07,993
I don't know her address.

62
00:06:11,663 --> 00:06:14,374
I guess I could've
tracked her down if I tried.

63
00:06:17,294 --> 00:06:18,420
But, I just...

64
00:06:23,425 --> 00:06:25,176
Have you seen her since then?

65
00:06:27,554 --> 00:06:28,637
Yeah.

66
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:30,891
What, really? When? Where?

67
00:06:32,183 --> 00:06:34,686
Last year, in Omiya.

68
00:06:35,937 --> 00:06:38,398
She was with her boyfriend.

69
00:06:39,274 --> 00:06:41,568
Apparently, she lives in Utsunomiya now.

70
00:06:42,861 --> 00:06:44,321
Is she doing all right?

71
00:06:45,322 --> 00:06:46,573
Yeah.

72
00:06:48,116 --> 00:06:50,619
She said she's "happy and stuff."

73
00:06:52,037 --> 00:06:53,246
Right.

74
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:02,922
I see...

75
00:07:07,677 --> 00:07:11,264
Funny... I've just been left behind.

76
00:07:12,557 --> 00:07:14,809
I drove you guys out of town.

77
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:20,565
And I couldn't stop Nanako
from leaving, either.

78
00:07:22,025 --> 00:07:23,276
Back then...

79
00:07:24,235 --> 00:07:26,905
what should I have done?

80
00:07:27,781 --> 00:07:29,406
I'm the only one

81
00:07:29,407 --> 00:07:31,992
that's been trapped in this town.

82
00:07:31,993 --> 00:07:34,913
Forever and ever...

83
00:07:35,955 --> 00:07:37,165
I don't want that...

84
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:49,010
What about Nakamura?

85
00:07:52,222 --> 00:07:55,725
What happened between you two after that?

86
00:08:00,063 --> 00:08:01,523
I haven't seen her.

87
00:08:03,441 --> 00:08:06,111
Not since the moment
she pushed me off the stage.

88
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:11,199
I don't know... where she is now.

89
00:08:13,368 --> 00:08:14,744
Whether she's alive,

90
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:18,540
or if she's dead.

91
00:08:22,377 --> 00:08:24,295
Don't you want to see her again?

92
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:28,883
I hope I can see her again, someday.

93
00:08:31,344 --> 00:08:32,387
Do you want to know?

94
00:08:34,097 --> 00:08:35,932
Do you want to know where she is now?

95
00:08:38,977 --> 00:08:39,978
What?
:cue

96
00:08:42,021 --> 00:08:43,731
-  You're lying.
-  It's crazy.

97
00:08:43,732 --> 00:08:46,234
You have to be lying.
That can't be true.

98
00:08:48,486 --> 00:08:50,612
Oh... Mornin'.

99
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:51,614
Morning.

100
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:54,075
How was Gunma?

101
00:08:54,701 --> 00:08:56,076
Got any souvenirs for us?

102
00:08:56,077 --> 00:08:59,497
Who comes back from a funeral
with souvenirs, idiot?

103
00:09:00,290 --> 00:09:04,585
You know, Tokiwa was feeling lonely
with you absent for two days.

104
00:09:04,586 --> 00:09:06,962
She wouldn't shut up about you.

105
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:09,131
Hey, that wasn't all I talked about!

106
00:09:21,144 --> 00:09:23,020
Hey, Kasuga?

107
00:09:23,021 --> 00:09:24,064
Yeah?

108
00:09:25,940 --> 00:09:27,025
If you're free today,

109
00:09:27,525 --> 00:09:30,528
why don't you come over to my place?

110
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:46,043
- Sorry.
- Hmm?

111
00:09:46,044 --> 00:09:48,588
I should've told you my parents were out.

112
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:51,424
No, don't worry about it.

113
00:09:53,301 --> 00:09:54,719
The thing is...

114
00:09:58,556 --> 00:09:59,641
I've finished...

115
00:10:01,017 --> 00:10:02,310
my novel.

116
00:10:02,977 --> 00:10:04,061
What?

117
00:10:04,062 --> 00:10:05,688
Seriously? When?

118
00:10:06,272 --> 00:10:07,482
Last night.

119
00:10:23,331 --> 00:10:24,707
Please read it.

120
00:10:29,462 --> 00:10:30,463
Tokiwa...

121
00:10:31,798 --> 00:10:32,924
Congratulations.

122
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:36,052
But...

123
00:10:38,179 --> 00:10:39,806
I can't read it right now.

124
00:10:42,016 --> 00:10:43,101
There's something...

125
00:10:44,978 --> 00:10:46,771
I need to tell you.

126
00:10:56,739 --> 00:10:57,907
You see,

127
00:10:59,784 --> 00:11:01,202
when I was in junior high,

128
00:11:02,829 --> 00:11:05,165
I made a contract with someone.

129
00:11:17,302 --> 00:11:18,969
That town,

130
00:11:18,970 --> 00:11:21,097
the town I was born and raised in,

131
00:11:21,681 --> 00:11:25,977
is a depressing town
surrounded by mountains.

132
00:11:28,479 --> 00:11:30,148
In my second year of junior high,

133
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:34,861
I stole the gym clothes
of the girl I had a crush on.

134
00:11:38,031 --> 00:11:39,824
I didn't mean to, though.

135
00:11:41,034 --> 00:11:42,326
I just...

136
00:11:42,327 --> 00:11:46,873
found it on the classroom floor,
and I took it home with me.

137
00:11:47,874 --> 00:11:51,878
This classmate named Nakamura saw me...

138
00:11:52,462 --> 00:11:53,670
SAEKI

139
00:11:53,671 --> 00:11:55,048
...and I ended up

140
00:11:55,798 --> 00:11:58,760
making a contract with Nakamura.

141
00:12:00,845 --> 00:12:02,305
One day, the two of us

142
00:12:02,972 --> 00:12:05,141
destroyed our classroom.

143
00:12:05,642 --> 00:12:08,268
We snuck into the school at night,

144
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:10,437
used the calligraphy ink and paint,

145
00:12:10,438 --> 00:12:12,397
and turned the place upside down,

146
00:12:12,398 --> 00:12:14,399
changing the classroom

147
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:17,237
into a chaotic mess,
like no one had ever seen before.

148
00:12:17,904 --> 00:12:19,447
Then, during swimming class,

149
00:12:20,573 --> 00:12:22,784
I snuck into the girls' changing room,

150
00:12:23,493 --> 00:12:26,537
and I stole the panties
of every girl in my class.

151
00:12:27,997 --> 00:12:30,208
It's not like I wanted them or anything.

152
00:12:31,584 --> 00:12:32,960
All I wanted was...

153
00:12:32,961 --> 00:12:34,754
I wanted to make Nakamura...

154
00:12:37,131 --> 00:12:38,633
I just wanted

155
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:41,302
to see Nakamura laugh.

156
00:12:43,012 --> 00:12:44,222
But, after all,

157
00:12:46,099 --> 00:12:49,060
I never succeeded
in making her truly laugh.

158
00:12:51,854 --> 00:12:53,273
In the end,

159
00:12:53,982 --> 00:12:55,483
I decided

160
00:12:56,025 --> 00:12:57,986
to leave this world with her.

161
00:13:00,697 --> 00:13:01,990
But...

162
00:13:06,244 --> 00:13:08,413
even that was beyond my reach.
:cue

163
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:23,052
That's the reason I moved here.

164
00:13:36,024 --> 00:13:37,108
Sorry.

165
00:13:38,109 --> 00:13:39,610
You need to leave.

166
00:13:45,366 --> 00:13:47,118
I have to think about this alone.

167
00:13:48,828 --> 00:13:49,954
Please.

168
00:13:52,582 --> 00:13:53,790
I can't leave.

169
00:13:53,791 --> 00:13:54,792
Why?

170
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:57,003
You're done with your story, right?

171
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:03,508
What do you want from me?

172
00:14:03,509 --> 00:14:05,594
I don't want anything from you.

173
00:14:05,595 --> 00:14:07,971
I just felt like I should tell you.

174
00:14:07,972 --> 00:14:09,766
Don't you think you're being selfish?

175
00:14:10,767 --> 00:14:13,144
All I asked was for you to read my novel.

176
00:14:13,978 --> 00:14:16,313
Did you just want to get this
off your chest?

177
00:14:16,314 --> 00:14:18,900
- No, it's not like that.
- What is it, then?

178
00:14:20,026 --> 00:14:21,152
I...

179
00:14:22,487 --> 00:14:24,363
I don't want to run from it anymore.

180
00:14:25,490 --> 00:14:28,450
Honestly, I thought I'd keep it to myself.

181
00:14:28,451 --> 00:14:30,828
That it'd be selfish
to make you deal with this.

182
00:14:32,497 --> 00:14:33,498
But...

183
00:14:35,625 --> 00:14:37,543
the past won't go away.

184
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:40,213
I realized

185
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:43,257
I still can't let go of Nakamura.

186
00:14:44,467 --> 00:14:46,469
It's not about liking her or not.

187
00:14:47,804 --> 00:14:49,597
I can't tell if I want to hold her

188
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:52,016
or be killed by her.

189
00:14:54,227 --> 00:14:55,394
I just...

190
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:59,273
I just want to see Nakamura again.

191
00:15:02,068 --> 00:15:03,861
So that I can find a life with you.

192
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:13,162
Nakamura's whereabouts are in this note.

193
00:15:14,122 --> 00:15:16,666
I got it the other day
from a classmate in Gunma.

194
00:15:18,835 --> 00:15:21,587
After I see Nakamura one more time,

195
00:15:22,588 --> 00:15:24,590
if you'd still forgive me...

196
00:15:26,717 --> 00:15:28,094
then...

197
00:15:28,845 --> 00:15:30,972
I'd like to read your novel.

198
00:15:36,352 --> 00:15:37,895
The answer is no.

199
00:15:40,523 --> 00:15:42,108
I can't let you read this.

200
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:48,197
This seems so silly now, all of a sudden.

201
00:16:02,795 --> 00:16:04,005
Tokiwa!

202
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:07,675
Wait!

203
00:16:08,551 --> 00:16:09,594
Stop it!

204
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:15,766
Wait!

205
00:16:17,602 --> 00:16:19,145
Let go of me!

206
00:16:19,812 --> 00:16:21,229
I said, let go!

207
00:16:21,230 --> 00:16:23,649
I won't let go of you, ever!

208
00:16:35,745 --> 00:16:36,746
Then...

209
00:16:37,288 --> 00:16:38,789
can you kiss me?

210
00:17:27,380 --> 00:17:28,673
I'll go with you.

211
00:17:29,757 --> 00:17:30,841
What?

212
00:17:32,093 --> 00:17:34,262
I'll go with you to see Nakamura.

213
00:17:43,729 --> 00:17:44,897
:cue

214
00:18:04,125 --> 00:18:10,256
NAKAMURA IS WITH HER MOTHER NOW,
HELPING OUT AT HER DINER IN TOKAWA, CHIBA.

215
00:18:21,517 --> 00:18:28,482
TOKAWA STATION

216
00:18:36,907 --> 00:18:38,034
Let's go.

217
00:18:38,826 --> 00:18:39,827
Okay.

218
00:18:59,597 --> 00:19:00,889
GUEST HOUSE CHONAN-SO

219
00:19:00,890 --> 00:19:02,058
Excuse me.

220
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:03,767
Yes?

221
00:19:03,768 --> 00:19:07,355
Is there a diner around here?

222
00:19:07,855 --> 00:19:10,607
Sure, there are a few.

223
00:19:10,608 --> 00:19:12,817
One that's run by a mother and daughter?

224
00:19:12,818 --> 00:19:17,490
Ah. You must be looking
for the Mizukoshi's, then.

225
00:19:18,115 --> 00:19:19,158
Mizukoshi Diner.

226
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:22,703
It's at the end of this road,

227
00:19:23,329 --> 00:19:24,955
but they close at 3:00 p.m.

228
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:27,123
I see.

229
00:19:27,124 --> 00:19:28,584
Thank you very much.

230
00:19:35,466 --> 00:19:36,801
Ah.

231
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:41,013
MIZUKOSHI DINER

232
00:19:50,648 --> 00:19:53,818
OPENING HOURS 11:00 A.M. - 3:00 P.M.
4:30 P.M. - 8:00 P.M.

233
00:20:01,826 --> 00:20:04,077
Hey, you've got customers.

234
00:20:04,078 --> 00:20:05,079
Coming!

235
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:07,790
Hello there, welcome.

236
00:20:08,290 --> 00:20:09,291
A table for two?

237
00:20:10,668 --> 00:20:12,794
- Yes, please.
-  Right over here.

238
00:20:12,795 --> 00:20:14,963
-  Thanks for lunch!
-  Thank you.

239
00:20:14,964 --> 00:20:18,049
You must be busy
without your girl helping out.

240
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:20,511
-  Come again soon.
- Will do.

241
00:20:26,183 --> 00:20:27,475
Hmm?

242
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:29,311
Please sit.

243
00:20:36,485 --> 00:20:38,654
Is that... her mom?

244
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:46,787
Have you decided on your order?

245
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:50,206
I'll have the fried mackerel set meal.

246
00:20:50,207 --> 00:20:51,291
All right.

247
00:20:51,292 --> 00:20:52,375
And you?

248
00:20:52,376 --> 00:20:55,044
I'll have... the same thing.
:cue

249
00:20:55,045 --> 00:20:57,339
Sure. I'll have those out in a bit.

250
00:21:41,008 --> 00:21:42,593
It smells like...

251
00:21:43,969 --> 00:21:45,178
I'm back.

252
00:21:45,179 --> 00:21:46,305
Welcome back.

253
00:21:49,433 --> 00:21:51,518
They only had
small bottles of soy sauce.

254
00:21:51,519 --> 00:21:53,354
I see. Thanks for getting these.

255
00:21:54,188 --> 00:21:56,857
- Take this to that table, would you?
-  Sure.

256
00:22:02,404 --> 00:22:05,699
Here's the fried mackerel set meal.

257
00:22:07,409 --> 00:22:09,495
I'll be back with another.

258
00:22:12,915 --> 00:22:14,165
Hey!

259
00:22:15,417 --> 00:22:16,877
Nakamura...

260
00:22:18,337 --> 00:22:20,130
Do you remember me?

261
00:22:21,966 --> 00:22:23,217
It's me, Kasuga.

262
00:22:24,051 --> 00:22:25,511
Takao Kasuga.

263
00:22:27,429 --> 00:22:28,972
I came to see you.

264
00:22:48,617 --> 00:22:50,869
TO BE CONTINUED

265
00:23:47,927 --> 00:23:49,010
ON THE NEXT EPISODE

266
00:23:49,011 --> 00:23:52,847
Kasuga and Nakamura
are reunited.

267
00:23:52,848 --> 00:23:56,643
Tokiwa quietly watches over them.

268
00:23:56,644 --> 00:24:01,856
Next, on the final episode,
see the other side of The Flowers of Evil.

269
00:24:01,857 --> 00:24:02,858
Translated by Yuka Kristi
